[src:voice-cloning-ml/deepfake-p02] In this deepfake, Peele's voice and face were transformed and manipulated into those of Obama.
[src:voice-cloning-ml/deepfake-p02] The intent of this video was to portray the dangerous consequences and power of deepfakes, and how deepfakes can make anyone say anything.
[src:voice-cloning-ml/deepfake-p02] In the original skit (aired 4 May 2016), Jimmy Fallon dressed as Donald Trump and pretended to participate in a phone call with Barack Obama, conversing in a manner that presented him to be bragging about his primary win in Indiana.
[src:voice-cloning-ml/deepfake-p02] In the deepfake, Jimmy Fallon's face was transformed into Donald Trump's face, with the audio remaining the same.
[src:voice-cloning-ml/deepfake-p02] This deepfake video was produced by Derpfakes with a comedic intent.
[src:voice-cloning-ml/deepfake-p02] In March 2023, a series of images appeared to show New York Police Department officers restraining Trump.
[src:voice-cloning-ml/deepfake-p02] but were later re-shared without context, leading some viewers to believe they were real photographs.
